{
  "texts": [
    "In this way, we can refine the partial sequence while effectively reverting to a previous scale by discarding the newly encoded finer-scale tokens.",
    "Incorporating this VAR-based \"scale-travel\" module into the autoregressive generation process significantly enhances realism, helping to overcome the diversity-realism trade-off caused by noise injection.",
    "Related Work Autoregressive Visual GenerationBuilding on the success of the transformer-based autoregressive (AR) modeling in LLMs [6,65], researchers have increasingly explored similar techniques for image generation.",
    "In the image domain, AR methods differ primarily by the order in which they process local patches (or tokens).",
    "First, (1) raster-scan order AR methods take an analogous approach to language modeling by flattening and quantizing a 2D image into a 1D sequence of discrete tokens, and then training an AR model for next-token prediction [9, 15, 16, 29, 50-52, 56, 58, 62, 63, 70, 79]."
  ]
